cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.MM, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the relationship between social behavior and popularity on a live-streaming platform. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of social media promotion on success and influence. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper examines community-defined behavioral norms and their impact on popularity. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper focuses on live video-streaming platforms and their content creators. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the behavior of content creators and their interaction with the platform and audience.
